			<div id="unique-entry-id-485" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Family Stories</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Monday, 09 July 2012 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="books" src="files/books.jpg" width="42" height="40" /></div>I am always on the look out for good family stories that suit small children as well as adults.  I have found another good set to add to the list of recommendations.  But for a change this is a set of four books of short stories about two regular chapters long.<br /><br />An author called Ed Wicke (http://www.blacknbluepress.info/edhome.html) visited my daughters school.  The first time I saw him i was in the hall and he swept off this hat and bowed to the kids around me.  The kids loved it, the next time I saw him he was sitting outside school selling and signing some of his books.  We bought wicked tales four, or the purple one as my daughter calls it.  Last Friday he returned to sell and sign more, so we had to get the first three to complete the set.<br /><br />We loved wicked tales four, especially the page before the story starts on the voices, my daughter with her large brown eyes can do the kitten's look very well (she not a confident reader yet an so no voices).  When my husband read a story he could not stay in a Florida accent and so the pair of Gaiters were scouse in the end.<br /><br />So if the accents do not start the giggles going the stories and occasional picture will. I don't usually like baby stories but reading about a baby throwing toys out of a cot each one named (Ted the toy tractor) even had me in giggles.<br /><br />So if you are looking for short stories as funny as Jeremy Strong's please give Ed Wicke's Wicked Tales a go.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-489" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Rather slow here</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Sunday, 08 July 2012 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-side-tracked.php">Side Tracked</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><img class="imageStyle" alt="mouse" src="files/mouse.jpg" width="41" height="41" /></div>For those of you wondering, yes I have not updated here for a while.  I am rather behind and it looks as if Vampirates central www.vampirates.co.uk is doing a very good job of keeping everyone informed.  So I have added in the three missing entries on the correct dates according to their list.  It is lovely to see Vampirates are still all around the world, Argentina, Australia, Brazil, Canada, Croatia, Ecuador, England, Ireland, Italy, Luxembourg, Malta, Mexico, Northern Ireland, Norway, Peru, Philippines, Poland, Portugal, Romania , Saudi Arabia, Scotland, Spain, Sweden, United States and of course Wales.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-487" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">Audiobooks</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 04 July 2012 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-vampirates.php">Vampirates</a></span><span class="blog-entry-category"> <a href="files/category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="files/vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a></div>If you like listening to your stories there is good news on the horizon.  Until the end of the school holidays (31 August 2012), Whole Story Audio Books are giving a 30% discount on all Vampirates unabridged audiobooks when the code VAMP-IRAT-EWEB-SITE is typed in the basket at there website.<br /><br />Please see <a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/whole-story-audio-books-promotio/" rel="self">www.vampirates.co.uk/whole-story-audio-books-promotio</a> or <a href="http://www.wholestoryaudiobooks.co.uk/catalogue/artist/author/justin_somper/1036" rel="self">www.wholestoryaudiobooks.co.uk/catalogue/artist/author/justin_somper/1036</a> for more information.<br /></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-488" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">La Guerra Inmortal</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Thursday, 28 June 2012 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-books.php">Books</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="files/vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a>La Guerra Inmortal has been released in Spain and to those of us like me that do not speak spanish, our spanish members of the crew how have their own copies of Immortal War.</div></div></div><div id="unique-entry-id-486" class="blog-entry"><h1 class="blog-entry-title">New Website</h1><div class="blog-entry-date">Wednesday, 30 May 2012 Filed in: <span class="blog-entry-category"><a href="files/category-vampirates.php">Vampirates</a></span></div><div class="blog-entry-body"><div class="image-left"><a href="http://www.vampirates.co.uk/" rel="external" title="www.vampirates.co.uk"><img class="imageStyle" alt="vampirates" src="files/vampirates.jpg" width="40" height="40" /></a>Please check out the new website.  It looks completely new.  Also it no longer has the sound effects so my volume can stay on.</div></div></div>
